<br>
thanks alot for the help..  appreciate it... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uleandrasilvertongue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leandra Silvertongue</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/27/01 6:20:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need help as a 37 Druid on wisdom desperately</span><hr size=1> I have a very low WIS - 90 base - so getting to 200 was very very tough for me (actually just made it to 200 last week).  Some of the Kunark quest armors have good WIS if you can get your guild to help you out.<br>
<br>
Another option - bind in Dagnor's Cauldron and look for Bilge.  I got a PKT when I was in my late 40's and it helped trememdously.  The -9STR hurts, but the +18 WIS is nice =)  If you can't camp it, you can probably buy it for around 10 - 12K I think.<br>
<br>
There is also a range item that drops outside the Frozen tower in IC that gives +4 WIS and +10 vs. cold.  The benefit of that over the medicine totem is weight - it is one wis less but weights only 1.0 opposed to 6.0 for the medicine totem.   <p><BR> Leandra  Silvertongue - Druid, 56  <BR> Proud member of <a href=http://pub49.ezboard.com/belysium55949>Elysium</a>  <BR>  <b>"Have you hugged a Druid today? =)" </b> <BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulyberniabelisama.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lybernia Belisama</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.sherilyn.net/pendulum/icon.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/27/01 6:36:21 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.columbus.rr.com/sherilyn70/lybernia4a.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need help as a 37 Druid on wisdom desperately</span><hr size=1> Wow, someone has lower wisdom than me.  :)  I thought I was bad with 94.  I didn't realize you had started her with such a low wisdom.  <br>
