13th level Bard</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uleandrasilvertongue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leandra Silvertongue</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/27/01 9:32:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need help as a 37 Druid on wisdom desperately</span><hr size=1> Actually, the Effy boots is something you can do outside of a guild.  With a good group of 50+ you can break effy with only one group (assuming you have a good chanter).  Last time we did it, we had a 60 Bard, me, 56 chanter, 58 Pally, 54 Shaman and 56 Cleric I belive.  Once you break, you only really need 4 people to hold that room - since there are only 3 spawns in there (assuming you stay inside and don't mess with the stuff outside).<br>
<br>
In terms of the Pkt - that is pure luck.  Bilge drops it in Dagnor's cauldron, he is a goblin in the low 30's in terms of level - so it is an easy kill - but he is an extremely rare spawn =/  He also drops the reed belt which gives either +5 or +6 Wis.  You can easily solo him if you can get him.  He has been known to drop both items so it's kind of a jackpot if you do get him =)<br>
<br>
Good luck and let me know if you need any help =)<br>
